# 4. Workflows

## A. Field Registration Workflow

1. Field executive visits customer  
2. Opens registration form  
3. Patient details are entered  
4. Family member details are added  
5. Consent is captured  
6. Documents are uploaded  
7. Membership plan is selected  
8. Health card number is generated  
9. Digital card PDF is created  
10. Card is shared through WhatsApp  
11. Status updated as issued / distributed

---

## B. Customer Access Workflow

1. Customer logs in using OTP or card number  
2. Views card dashboard  
3. Views digital health card  
4. Checks family members  
5. Sees service history and notifications  
6. Contacts support or views updates

---

## C. Hospital Retrieval Workflow

1. Customer arrives at hospital  
2. Reception searches by card number / phone / name / QR  
3. Patient profile is retrieved  
4. Identity is verified  
5. Patient is checked in  
6. Visit or service is recorded  
7. Billing / discount applied if required  
8. Confirmation message sent

---

## D. Admin Control Workflow

1. Admin logs in  
2. Accesses dashboard  
3. Reviews registrations, usage, revenue  
4. Manages users, roles, hospitals, plans, settings  
5. Monitors logs, reports, alerts

---

# 5. Rules

## Registration Rules

- Mobile number should be unique or flagged for duplicate review
- Required fields must be completed before submission
- Consent must be captured before card generation
- Family members must link under correct main customer
- Documents required as per policy

## Card Rules

- Every card must have a unique card number
- Card validity must be defined
- Status must track active / expired / suspended / reissued
- Card should reflect family coverage

## Access Rules

- Every user must have a role
- Every role must have defined permissions
- Users only see menus/pages allowed by role
- Sensitive admin functions restricted

## Hospital Rules

- Search should support multiple identifiers
- Users access only allowed branch data
- Visit records stored for every service entry
- Discounts / claims follow approved rules

## Communication Rules

- Messages triggered only by approved events
- Failed WhatsApp / SMS delivery logged
- Resend options controlled
- Templates approved before use

## Data Rules

- Patient and family data stored securely
- Audit logs record key actions
- Critical records support traceability
- Backups maintained

---

# 6. Edge Cases

## Registration

- Duplicate phone number
- Missing mandatory fields
- Invalid OTP
- No network during registration
- Incomplete family details
- Document upload failure

## Card

- Card generation fails
- PDF generation fails
- WhatsApp message fails
- Card number duplication
- Card expiry before activation

## Hospital

- Patient not found
- Wrong card number entered
- Similar patient names
- QR scan failure
- Branch not authorised
- Visit recorded twice

## Permission

- Role changed while logged in
- Sidebar shows menu but API blocks access
- Revoked permission cached
- Excess access assigned accidentally

## Communication

- WhatsApp template rejected
- Queue delayed
- SMS gateway outage
- Invalid number
- Retry exceeds limit

## Business

- Card reissue request
- Renewal after expiry
- Family member removed
- Patient transfer between hospitals
- Revenue / discount mismatch

---

# 7. Compliance

## Security & Privacy Compliance

- Consent management recorded
- Access to patient data role-based
- Audit trail for important changes
- Data in transit encrypted
- Data at rest encrypted
- Sensitive documents stored securely
- Login and activity logs retained
- Backup and recovery process exists
- Privacy rules enforced

## Operational Compliance

- Only authorised staff can access patient info
- Administrative actions traceable
- Communication records auditable
- Billing / discount changes reviewable
- Retention and deletion rules defined

## Future Compliance Readiness

The system should support stronger healthcare/privacy regulations later without major redesign.